comfortable here for a while.

255
00:32:21,388 --> 00:32:23,413
I'll see to it that you have
everything you need.

256
00:35:45,592 --> 00:35:46,820
Cor blimey!

257
00:35:52,165 --> 00:35:55,931
So, this is the Elephant Man.

258
00:35:57,503 --> 00:35:59,994
I ain't seen nothing
like you before.

259
00:36:02,308 --> 00:36:04,902
What the bleedin' hell
happened to ya?

260
00:36:09,449 --> 00:36:11,110
Dumb, eh?

261
00:36:12,819 --> 00:36:15,617
I like people
that can keep quiet.

262
00:36:19,025 --> 00:36:21,823
Here, have a drink.

263
00:36:24,497 --> 00:36:26,829
Go on! No?

264
00:36:31,471 --> 00:36:33,996
You should be more sociable, mate.

265
00:36:36,175 --> 00:36:38,405
You'll get yourself disliked.

266
00:36:43,683 --> 00:36:47,050
You and I are
gonna be good friends...

267
00:36:47,120 --> 00:36:49,384
and I've got a lot of friends
who'd like to meet you.

268
00:36:49,455 --> 00:36:51,548
And they will, mate.

269
00:36:51,624 --> 00:36:54,525
Believe me, they will.

270
00:37:05,638 --> 00:37:09,005
I've brought your breakfast.
What are you doing down there?

271
00:37:09,075 --> 00:37:11,202
Come on, up on the bed.

272
00:37:48,081 --> 00:37:50,606
All he understands
is a good smack.

273
00:37:50,683 --> 00:37:54,312
He's had his share of smacks. That's
what drives him under the bed.

274
00:37:54,387 --> 00:37:57,117
You have to treat him
with kindness and patience.

275
00:37:57,190 --> 00:38:00,853
Perhaps you've got time for that
sort of treatment, Mr. Treves.

276
00:38:00,927 --> 00:38:03,896
But I haven't.
I've got a hospital to run.

277
00:38:03,963 --> 00:38:06,124
Now, don't you waste your time
with him, sir.

278
00:38:07,567 --> 00:38:11,025
It's like talking to a brick wall.

279
00:38:11,104 --> 00:38:15,473
Now, I don't mean to be harsh but...

280
00:38:15,541 --> 00:38:17,509
he doesn't belong here.

281
00:38:19,412 --> 00:38:24,509
Honestly, sir, honestly,
what can you do for him?

282
00:38:36,896 --> 00:38:40,593
Oh, and by the way,
Mr. Carr Gomm said...

283
00:38:40,666 --> 00:38:43,635
he would like to see you
when you can spare a moment.

284
00:38:43,703 --> 00:38:45,364
- Yes.
- Right.

285
00:38:51,444 --> 00:38:53,708
I can't help you
unless you help me.

286
00:39:02,722 --> 00:39:06,419
You see, I believe there's something
that you want to say to me.

287
00:39:06,492 --> 00:39:09,188
Something back there.

288
00:39:09,262 --> 00:39:11,753
I can't help you unless
you help me, you know!

289
00:39:15,068 --> 00:39:17,969
I believe you want to say something
to me, don't you?

290
00:39:19,639 --> 00:39:23,006
I've got to understand what you're
feeling, what you're thinking.

291
00:39:24,710 --> 00:39:26,803
Do you understand me?

292
00:39:29,949 --> 00:39:33,646
All right, just nod your head
if you can... Can you understand me?

293
00:39:33,719 --> 00:39:36,449
Just nod your head
if you understand me.

294
00:39:41,227 --> 00:39:42,751
All right.

295
00:39:44,630 --> 00:39:46,962
You do understand.

296
00:39:47,033 --> 00:39:49,558
I want to hear...
I want to hear you talk.

297
00:39:49,635 --> 00:39:52,468
We're gonna show them that
you're not a wall. Understand?

298
00:39:52,538 --> 00:39:55,302
I want you to talk to me.

299
00:39:55,374 --> 00:39:59,333
All right, now,
I want to hear you say it.

300
00:39:59,412 --> 00:40:01,937
I've got to hear how
you say things.

301
00:40:02,014 --> 00:40:06,451
I won't hurt you. I've got to hear
and understand how you say things.

302
00:40:06,519 --> 00:40:09,920
Very slowly,
I want you to say, "Yes."

303
00:40:12,024 --> 00:40:13,286
Say, "Yes."

304
00:40:18,631 --> 00:40:20,496
Yes.

305
00:40:21,601 --> 00:40:23,091
Yes!

306
00:40:23,169 --> 00:40:24,602
Good.

307
00:40:25,338 --> 00:40:28,739
All right, now, just once more
say it again. "Yes."

308
00:40:33,579 --> 00:40:36,207
Yes, I can understand that.

309
00:40:36,282 --> 00:40:37,749
That's good.

310
00:40:38,918 --> 00:40:40,909
That's very good.
All right now.

311
00:40:40,987 --> 00:40:43,979
I'm going to say some words to you,
and I want you to repeat them.

312
00:40:44,056 --> 00:40:46,286
Do you understand?

313
00:40:46,359 --> 00:40:48,759
Say, "Hello.

314
00:40:48,828 --> 00:40:50,591
My name is..."

315
00:40:55,201 --> 00:40:56,634
Hello.

316
00:40:57,904 --> 00:41:00,668
My name is...

317
00:41:00,740 --> 00:41:03,368
"John Merrick."

318
00:41:06,112 --> 00:41:09,343
No. John... That's very good.

319
00:41:09,415 --> 00:41:11,610
Say, "John Merrick."

320
00:41:16,088 --> 00:41:20,218
"Hello. My name is John Merrick."

321
00:41:22,395 --> 00:41:23,692
Hello.

322
00:41:23,763 --> 00:41:27,130
My name is...

323
00:41:27,200 --> 00:41:29,828
John Merrick.

324
00:41:29,902 --> 00:41:31,233
You can speak.

325
00:41:39,912 --> 00:41:41,903
How did you get up here?

326
00:41:43,416 --> 00:41:45,384
I want my man back.

327
00:41:45,451 --> 00:41:50,081
- Just a moment. How did you get up?
- Never mind that. I want my man.

328
00:41:50,156 --> 00:41:52,090
He's still very sick.

329
00:41:52,158 --> 00:41:54,558
Please, come downstairs with me,
and I'll explain the situation.

330
00:41:54,627 --> 00:41:56,254
Don't!

331
00:41:57,663 --> 00:41:59,756
Don't.

332
00:41:59,832 --> 00:42:03,859
You've had plenty of time to...

333
00:42:03,936 --> 00:42:06,097
cure him.

334
00:42:06,172 --> 00:42:08,868
And now he's leaving with me.

335
00:42:08,941 --> 00:42:14,174
Do you understand me now,
Mr. Treves?

336
00:42:14,247 --> 00:42:15,976
We made a deal.

337
00:42:16,048 --> 00:42:17,845
You misunderstood.

338
00:42:17,917 --> 00:42:22,547
This man has suffered a severe fall,
if you take my meaning.

339
00:42:22,622 --> 00:42:24,419
He's my patient now.

340
00:42:24,490 --> 00:42:26,515
Pull the other one,
why don't you?

341
00:42:26,592 --> 00:42:28,526
Mr. Bytes, I'm sorry.

342
00:42:28,594 --> 00:42:31,062
But all you do is profit
from another man's misery.

343
00:42:33,165 --> 00:42:35,156
Do you think
you're better than me?

344
00:42:35,234 --> 00:42:37,168
No, I never said that.

345
00:42:37,236 --> 00:42:40,831
You wanted the freak...

346
00:42:40,906 --> 00:42:44,364
to show to those doctor chums of
yours, to make a name for yourself.

347
00:42:44,443 --> 00:42:46,411
You, my friend.

348
00:42:47,980 --> 00:42:53,077
I gave you the freak on trust...

349
00:42:53,152 --> 00:42:56,212
in the name of science...

350
00:42:56,289 --> 00:42:58,257
and now I want him back!

351
00:42:58,357 --> 00:43:00,382
You do not own this man!
Now stop it!

352
00:43:01,294 --> 00:43:03,091
I want him back!

353
00:43:03,162 --> 00:43:05,221
So you can beat him?
So you can starve him?

354
00:43:05,298 --> 00:43:07,664
A dog in the streets
would fare better with you!

355
00:43:07,733 --> 00:43:09,869
I shall go to the authorities.

356
00:43:09,869 --> 00:43:13,270
Go to the authorities then!
Go to them by all means.

357
00:43:13,372 --> 00:43:16,739
They'll be very interested
to hear your story as well as ours.

358
00:43:18,477 --> 00:43:20,536
Now...

359
00:43:20,613 --> 00:43:25,073
I think we really do understand
one another.

360
00:43:28,120 --> 00:43:29,553
All right.

361
00:43:44,537 --> 00:43:47,734
Singularly unattractive character,
I must say.

362
00:43:49,575 --> 00:43:53,671
Well, Treves, it seems to me I might
as well meet this patient of yours.

363
00:43:53,746 --> 00:43:57,147
Thank you very much.
Thank you.

364
00:44:00,019 --> 00:44:02,146
Shall we say in a few days then?

365
00:44:02,221 --> 00:44:04,485
Shall we say 2:00
tomorrow afternoon?

366
00:44:08,127 --> 00:44:11,392
Yes. Well, whatever's
most convenient for you, sir.

367
00:44:11,464 --> 00:44:13,864
2:00 then, tomorrow.

368
00:44:13,933 --> 00:44:15,958
Thank you very much.

369
00:44:20,272 --> 00:44:21,705
2:00!

370
00:44:25,578 --> 00:44:28,012
Morning, Mr. Treves.
Early again, I see.

371
00:44:28,080 --> 00:44:29,342
Yes.

372
00:44:29,448 --> 00:44:32,440
With these early habits of yours,
you'd have made a good milkman.

373
00:44:32,551 --> 00:44:36,214
- I'll keep that in mind, Charles.
- Okay, sir. Good morning.

374
00:44:44,296 --> 00:44:47,322
He restoreth my soul.

375
00:44:47,433 --> 00:44:52,427
He leadeth me into paths of...
for His name's sake.

376
00:44:52,538 --> 00:44:55,905
Righteousness. Righteousness.

377
00:44:57,576 --> 00:45:02,172
He leadeth me in the paths
of righteousness...

378
00:45:02,248 --> 00:45:04,739
for His name's sake.

379
00:45:04,850 --> 00:45:07,876
Good. That's very good. Good.

380
00:45:07,987 --> 00:45:12,321
When your visitor comes today, say
it exactly the way you've said it.

381
00:45:12,391 --> 00:45:17,124
So when I introduce him to you,
say the words that you've learned.

382
00:45:17,196 --> 00:45:20,962
If you have trouble with any words,
I'll help you, so don't worry.

383
00:45:21,033 --> 00:45:23,501
I will introduce him to you
and say...

384
00:45:23,602 --> 00:45:26,002
"Please meet Mr. Carr Gomm."

385
00:45:26,071 --> 00:45:27,663
And you will say?

386
00:45:28,841 --> 00:45:33,471
Hello. My name is John Merrick.

387
00:45:33,546 --> 00:45:35,776
I'm very pleased to meet you.

388
00:45:37,082 --> 00:45:39,550
Good! Good.

389
00:45:39,652 --> 00:45:42,587
I'll go and get Mr. Carr Gomm.

390
00:45:48,227 --> 00:45:50,855
It is only a physical problem.

391
00:45:52,498 --> 00:45:55,262
He has trouble with certain sounds
because of...

392
00:45:55,334 --> 00:45:58,667
the constrictive deformity
of the mouth, but he can talk.

393
00:45:58,737 --> 00:46:02,571
Talking's one thing, but is he able
to understand what's said to him?

394
00:46:02,641 --> 00:46:05,610
Yes. Oh, yes! Except...

395
00:46:05,711 --> 00:46:09,670
Except he's so anxious to make
a good impression on you...

396
00:46:09,782 --> 00:46:11,977
that he might seem a little nervous.

397
00:46:29,835 --> 00:46:31,302
Come in.

398
00:46:45,484 --> 00:46:46,712
John...

399
00:46:46,785 --> 00:46:49,845
may I introduce you
to Mr. Carr Gomm?

400
00:46:49,955 --> 00:46:52,981
Mr. Carr Gomm,
this is John Merrick.

401
00:46:54,059 --> 00:46:57,620
Hello. My name is John Merrick.

402
00:46:57,696 --> 00:46:59,664
I'm very pleased to meet you.

403
00:46:59,765 --> 00:47:01,858
I'm very pleased to meet you.

404
00:47:04,503 --> 00:47:06,437
How are you feeling today?

405
00:47:06,505 --> 00:47:09,167
I feel much better.

406
00:47:10,643 --> 00:47:12,770
Are you comfortable here?

407
00:47:15,414 --> 00:47:18,508
Everybody's been very kind.

408
00:47:19,451 --> 00:47:21,442
How is your bronchitis?

409
00:47:33,666 --> 00:47:36,134
Mr. Merrick likes the food here,
don't you?

410
00:47:40,773 --> 00:47:44,265
Much better than what
I'm used to.

411
00:47:44,376 --> 00:47:46,071
Oh, yes?

412
00:47:47,012 --> 00:47:49,071
Yes. And what was that?

413
00:47:52,017 --> 00:47:53,450
Potatoes.

414
00:47:55,220 --> 00:47:57,245
I understood
that you'd been flogged.

415
00:48:00,292 --> 00:48:04,023
I feel much better now.

416
00:48:04,096 --> 00:48:05,529
That's splendid.

417
00:48:05,564 --> 00:48:08,556
How do you find Mr. Treves?

418
00:48:08,634 --> 00:48:10,795
As a teacher, I mean.

419
00:48:16,342 --> 00:48:20,938
Everybody's been very kind.

420
00:48:23,582 --> 00:48:27,916
How long did you and Mr. Treves
prepare for this interview?

421
00:48:34,693 --> 00:48:38,720
Everybody's been very kind.

422
00:48:38,831 --> 00:48:40,765
Yes, of course, I understand.

423
00:48:40,833 --> 00:48:43,802
Well, it's been a pleasure
meeting you, Mr. Merrick.

424
00:48:43,869 --> 00:48:45,996
Good day to you.

425
00:48:55,748 --> 00:48:57,613
Very good, John.

426
00:48:57,716 --> 00:48:59,616
It was very good.

427
00:48:59,718 --> 00:49:01,618
I'll be back in a moment.

428
00:49:05,724 --> 00:49:08,557
The Lord is my shepherd...

429
00:49:09,628 --> 00:49:11,960
I shall not want.

430
00:49:13,032 --> 00:49:14,966
He maketh me lie down...

431
00:49:15,034 --> 00:49:19,528
It was a brave attempt, but the man
was mouthing words taught by you.

432
00:49:19,638 --> 00:49:23,267
Yes. Well, I'm sorry
to have wasted your time.

433
00:49:23,342 --> 00:49:26,539
He restoreth my soul.

434
00:49:26,612 --> 00:49:28,375
He simply doesn't belong here.

435
00:49:28,447 --> 00:49:31,746
He'd be better off somewhere where
he can be constantly looked after.

436
00:49:31,817 --> 00:49:34,786
I'm sorry things have turned out
this way. Good day to you.

437
00:49:34,853 --> 00:49:36,286
Yea...

438
00:49:37,589 --> 00:49:41,116
though I walk through the valley
of the shadow of death...

439
00:49:41,226 --> 00:49:43,057
I fear no evil...

440
00:49:43,128 --> 00:49:45,961
for Thou art with me.

441
00:49:46,031 --> 00:49:48,499
Thy rod and staff, they...

442
00:49:48,567 --> 00:49:50,034
Mr. Carr Gomm!

443
00:49:52,538 --> 00:49:54,870
Yes, what is it?

444
00:49:54,940 --> 00:49:56,669
It's that.

445
00:49:58,310 --> 00:50:01,245
I didn't teach him that part.

446
00:50:02,948 --> 00:50:05,974
Surely goodness and mercy...

447
00:50:06,085 --> 00:50:09,350
will follow me all the days
of my life...

448
00:50:09,421 --> 00:50:14,415
and I'll dwell in the house
of the Lord forever.

449
00:50:18,464 --> 00:50:21,922
How did you know the rest of it?
I didn't teach you the rest of it.

450
00:50:22,034 --> 00:50:24,002
It's very strange.

451
00:50:25,237 --> 00:50:27,705
Tell me, how did you know
the rest of it?

452
00:50:27,773 --> 00:50:30,071
The 23rd Psalm.

453
00:50:33,278 --> 00:50:37,942
I used to read the Bible every day.

454
00:50:39,718 --> 00:50:42,346
I know it very well...

455
00:50:42,421 --> 00:50:44,719
and the Book of Common Prayer.

456
00:50:46,258 --> 00:50:50,194
The 23rd Psalm is very beautiful.
It's my favorite.

457
00:50:53,031 --> 00:50:56,159
Treves, come and see me in my office
when you're through up here.

458
00:50:56,235 --> 00:50:58,169
There's something important
I want to say to you.

459
00:50:59,505 --> 00:51:03,236
Good-bye, Mr. Merrick.
I do hope we shall meet again.

460
00:51:11,283 --> 00:51:14,912
Well, why didn't you tell me
you could read?

461
00:51:17,189 --> 00:51:20,022
I was frightened.

462
00:51:21,160 --> 00:51:22,354
I see.

463
00:51:22,427 --> 00:51:27,421
I was afraid to talk.

464
00:51:30,469 --> 00:51:33,199
Please forgive me.

465
00:51:43,115 --> 00:51:46,551
Can you imagine the kind of life
he must have had?

466
00:51:46,618 --> 00:51:48,518
Yes, I think I can.

467
00:51:48,587 --> 00:51:50,521
I don't believe so.

468
00:51:50,589 --> 00:51:54,582
No one could possibly imagine it.
I don't believe any of us can!

469
00:52:05,404 --> 00:52:07,338
"Terrible though
his appearance is...

470
00:52:07,406 --> 00:52:11,502
so terrible indeed that women
and nervous persons...

471
00:52:11,577 --> 00:52:14,978
fly in horror
from the sight of him...

472
00:52:15,047 --> 00:52:20,485
and that he is debarred from seeking
to earn his livelihood in any way...

473
00:52:20,552 --> 00:52:23,350
yet he is superior in intelligence.

474
00:52:23,422 --> 00:52:27,415
He can read and write,
he's quiet, gentle...

475
00:52:27,492 --> 00:52:31,326
not to say even refined
in his mind."

476
00:52:38,871 --> 00:52:42,102
I should very much like
to meet this gentleman.

477
00:53:08,834 --> 00:53:10,859
Have you seen this?

478
00:53:17,943 --> 00:53:19,376
Listen to this.

479
00:53:19,444 --> 00:53:21,469
Hey up! Hey up!

480
00:53:26,385 --> 00:53:28,046
Now listen.

481
00:53:28,120 --> 00:53:31,749
This is a letter
to the London Times...

482
00:53:31,823 --> 00:53:33,984
from the governor of the hospital.

483
00:53:35,160 --> 00:53:37,958
"There is now in a little room
off one of our attic wards...

484
00:53:38,030 --> 00:53:40,521
a man named John Merrick.

485
00:53:40,599 --> 00:53:42,760
So dreadful a sight
that he is unable...

486
00:53:42,834 --> 00:53:45,962
even to come out by daylight
to the garden.

487
00:53:46,038 --> 00:53:49,030
He is being called
the Elephant Man...

488
00:53:49,107 --> 00:53:51,632
on account of
his terrible deformity.

489
00:53:51,710 --> 00:53:56,647
His appearance is so terrible
that women and nervous persons...

490
00:53:56,715 --> 00:53:59,343
fly in terror
at the sight of him."

491
00:54:02,387 --> 00:54:04,912
And how do you get tickets
to see him?

492
00:54:04,990 --> 00:54:07,220
Your very own Sunny Jim.

493
00:54:07,292 --> 00:54:09,920
- Let's go and see him then!
- All right, keep your shirt on.

494
00:54:09,995 --> 00:54:12,293
The time must be right.

495
00:54:13,899 --> 00:54:15,867
Right now he's in the attic.

496
00:54:15,934 --> 00:54:21,338
But tomorrow they're moving him to
Bedstead Square right into my lap.

497
00:54:21,406 --> 00:54:24,864
Then, for the right price...

498
00:54:24,943 --> 00:54:30,040
you will see something you'll
never ever see again in your life!

499
00:55:19,531 --> 00:55:21,465
Well, don't look so glum, girls.

500
00:55:21,533 --> 00:55:25,367
Enthusiastic volunteers
should be more cheerful, hmm?

501
00:55:26,271 --> 00:55:28,967
Put your collar straight, girl.

502
00:55:29,041 --> 00:55:31,475
And remember...

503
00:55:31,543 --> 00:55:34,535
that under no circumstances...

504
00:55:34,613 --> 00:55:36,046
whatsoever...

505
00:55:38,216 --> 00:55:40,707
are any mirrors to be brought
into this room.

506
00:55:40,786 --> 00:55:42,754
Yes, Mrs. Mothershead.

507
00:55:43,989 --> 00:55:45,820
Yes.

508
00:55:45,891 --> 00:55:47,324
All right.

509
00:55:52,664 --> 00:55:57,431
- He's so ugly.
