01:18:28,888 --> 01:18:32,654
To parade them about in front of the
pathological society is one thing...

767
01:18:32,725 --> 01:18:34,818
but to waste this committee's
valuable time...

768
01:18:34,894 --> 01:18:39,228
with requests for shelter for these
abominations of nature is another.

769
01:18:44,237 --> 01:18:47,138
You must be more careful.

770
01:18:47,206 --> 01:18:51,233
In the light of these facts,
our course is clear.

771
01:18:51,310 --> 01:18:54,677
The question is not whether to
accept this creature as a patient.

772
01:18:54,747 --> 01:18:58,239
The question is, when will
those rooms be vacated for use...

773
01:18:58,317 --> 01:19:01,480
by better qualified,
more deserving cases?

774
01:19:01,554 --> 01:19:03,249
I move that this Elephant Man...

775
01:19:03,322 --> 01:19:05,813
be removed from
the premises immediately.

776
01:19:05,892 --> 01:19:09,623
We have a sacred duty
to cure the sick...

777
01:19:09,695 --> 01:19:11,287
not care for circus animals.

778
01:19:12,732 --> 01:19:16,099
That is my last word on the subject.
Mr. Chairman, shall we vote?

779
01:19:16,168 --> 01:19:19,763
I take it, Mr. Broadneck, your mind
is quite unshakable in this matter?

780
01:19:19,839 --> 01:19:22,933
Mr. Chairman,
do you not have ears?

781
01:19:23,009 --> 01:19:25,500
I am unalterably opposed!

782
01:19:26,279 --> 01:19:28,270
My mind is made up on this!

783
01:19:30,149 --> 01:19:32,242
You shall not sway me.

784
01:19:32,318 --> 01:19:36,152
May we now vote, Mr. Chairman,
at long last?

785
01:19:37,290 --> 01:19:38,780
Yes, Broadneck.

786
01:19:38,858 --> 01:19:40,792
I think the time has come.

787
01:19:41,861 --> 01:19:45,024
Gentlemen, Her Royal Highness...

788
01:19:45,097 --> 01:19:48,328
Alexandra, Princess of Wales.

789
01:20:06,218 --> 01:20:09,016
Good morning, gentlemen.
I hope I am not disturbing you.

790
01:20:09,088 --> 01:20:11,147
On the contrary, ma'am.
Your presence here...

791
01:20:11,223 --> 01:20:13,919
is always greatly appreciated.

792
01:20:13,993 --> 01:20:17,019
We were just taking a vote
on Mr. Merrick.

793
01:20:21,100 --> 01:20:24,900
Her Royal Highness has shown
the greatest interest in his fate.

794
01:20:24,971 --> 01:20:27,337
Indeed I have, sir,
as has the queen.

795
01:20:30,810 --> 01:20:33,540
I have a brief communication
from Her Majesty...

796
01:20:33,579 --> 01:20:36,070
which she has requested
that I read to you.

797
01:20:39,051 --> 01:20:42,020
"To the Governing Committee,
London Hospital.

798
01:20:49,662 --> 01:20:53,996
I would very much like to commend
you for the charitable face...

799
01:20:54,066 --> 01:20:56,967
you have shown Mr. John Merrick,
the Elephant Man.

800
01:20:57,036 --> 01:20:59,664
It is laudable
that you have provided...

801
01:20:59,739 --> 01:21:02,105
one of England's
most unfortunate sons...

802
01:21:02,174 --> 01:21:06,804
with a safe and tranquil harbor,
a home.

803
01:21:06,879 --> 01:21:08,779
For this immeasurable kindness...

804
01:21:08,848 --> 01:21:11,214
as well as the many
other acts of mercy...

805
01:21:11,283 --> 01:21:13,217
on behalf of the poor...

806
01:21:13,285 --> 01:21:17,415
of which Mr. Carr Gomm
has kept me informed...

807
01:21:17,490 --> 01:21:20,391
I gratefully thank you.

808
01:21:20,459 --> 01:21:22,086
Signed, Victoria."

809
01:21:27,199 --> 01:21:31,568
I'm sure I can count on you
gentlemen to do the Christian thing.

810
01:21:31,637 --> 01:21:35,266
Thank you very much, ma'am.
I'm sure we shall all try.

811
01:21:36,542 --> 01:21:39,170
Gentlemen, I wish to move
that Mr. John Merrick...

812
01:21:39,245 --> 01:21:41,645
be admitted to this hospital
on a permanent basis...

813
01:21:41,747 --> 01:21:44,944
provided the hospital receives
a yearly sum...

814
01:21:45,017 --> 01:21:47,747
equal to the cost of
the occupation of one bed.

815
01:21:48,454 --> 01:21:50,649
All those in favor?

816
01:22:02,301 --> 01:22:05,361
Thank you, gentlemen.
The motion is carried.

817
01:22:11,510 --> 01:22:13,876
Yes. Come in!

818
01:22:19,351 --> 01:22:20,943
Good afternoon.

819
01:22:22,588 --> 01:22:25,386
Mr. Carr Gomm has something
he wants to say to you.

820
01:22:25,458 --> 01:22:27,926
Mr. Merrick,
I have very great pleasure...

821
01:22:27,993 --> 01:22:30,757
in being able
to welcome you officially...

822
01:22:30,830 --> 01:22:32,559
to the London Hospital.

823
01:22:32,631 --> 01:22:35,327
This morning, the governing
committee unanimously voted...

824
01:22:35,401 --> 01:22:39,565
that you should be provided with
these rooms on a permanent basis.

825
01:22:39,638 --> 01:22:41,868
This is your home now.

826
01:22:41,941 --> 01:22:44,239
I'm so very, very glad for you.

827
01:22:44,310 --> 01:22:46,642
Welcome home, lad.

828
01:22:50,850 --> 01:22:52,442
This is...

829
01:22:54,487 --> 01:22:55,920
my home?

830
01:22:55,988 --> 01:22:57,148
Yes.

831
01:22:57,223 --> 01:23:02,183
Please, will you thank
the governing committee for me?

832
01:23:02,261 --> 01:23:04,195
I will do my utmost...

833
01:23:04,263 --> 01:23:07,198
to merit their kindness.

834
01:23:07,833 --> 01:23:09,926
This...

835
01:23:10,002 --> 01:23:12,163
is my home?

836
01:23:13,239 --> 01:23:15,207
Yes. This as well.

837
01:23:22,548 --> 01:23:23,879
Your dressing case.

838
01:23:33,058 --> 01:23:34,650
Oh, thank you.

839
01:23:41,267 --> 01:23:43,201
Thanks, all my friends.

840
01:23:43,269 --> 01:23:45,499
Thank you.

841
01:23:45,571 --> 01:23:48,768
- You like it?
- Oh, my friends.

842
01:23:54,313 --> 01:23:56,247
Oh, my friends.

843
01:23:58,784 --> 01:24:01,275
Oh, thank you.

844
01:24:25,978 --> 01:24:28,412
- Who's next?
- I say.

845
01:24:29,815 --> 01:24:32,283
- What, you again?
- Yeah, but...

846
01:24:32,351 --> 01:24:35,684
But these young ladies
have never seen it.

847
01:24:38,991 --> 01:24:40,583
You're on, mate.

848
01:24:43,229 --> 01:24:46,494
Okay, that's it
for this performance.

849
01:24:46,565 --> 01:24:50,001
- Jim, can I go tonight?
- Sit down, Charlie.

850
01:24:51,370 --> 01:24:53,304
There's always tomorrow.
Don't worry.

851
01:24:57,009 --> 01:24:59,534
Room for one more?

852
01:24:59,612 --> 01:25:01,546
At the right price.

853
01:25:03,449 --> 01:25:04,939
There's room.

854
01:25:16,862 --> 01:25:19,387
All right, all right!
Keep the noise down!

855
01:25:21,867 --> 01:25:24,335
We don't want
to frighten him, do we?

856
01:25:58,837 --> 01:26:01,169
Hello. My name...

857
01:26:01,240 --> 01:26:05,472
is John Merrick...

858
01:26:05,544 --> 01:26:09,776
and I'm very, very pleased...

859
01:26:09,848 --> 01:26:12,316
to meet you.

860
01:26:16,422 --> 01:26:19,050
I think you are...

861
01:26:19,124 --> 01:26:22,150
very beautiful...

862
01:26:25,731 --> 01:26:28,325
Curtain time!

863
01:26:28,400 --> 01:26:31,961
You look beautiful, darling.
I wouldn't change a thing.

864
01:26:33,072 --> 01:26:35,336
You look like
the bleedin' Prince of Wales.

865
01:26:37,309 --> 01:26:39,243
Here, my friends...

866
01:26:40,779 --> 01:26:42,508
is the Elephant Man!

867
01:26:45,617 --> 01:26:49,053
I told you he was horrible.

868
01:26:49,121 --> 01:26:50,713
Just horrible.

869
01:27:00,199 --> 01:27:03,293
Perhaps the ladies
would like a closer look?

870
01:27:03,369 --> 01:27:06,930
- Yeah, yeah.
- No, Jack!

871
01:27:11,010 --> 01:27:12,602
There.

872
01:27:14,913 --> 01:27:18,076
He's quite a ladies' man, isn't he?

873
01:27:18,150 --> 01:27:22,177
Come on. Give the ladies' man
a little kiss, eh?

874
01:27:23,489 --> 01:27:25,719
Come on.
Give him a kiss.

875
01:27:37,736 --> 01:27:40,466
Here, here, here!
That's enough romance.

876
01:27:40,539 --> 01:27:42,131
Time for beddy-byes.

877
01:28:32,558 --> 01:28:34,492
All right, all right.
Keep the noise down.

878
01:28:34,560 --> 01:28:37,120
Now, keep it quiet.
Quiet! Hey!

879
01:28:37,196 --> 01:28:39,164
Keep it quiet.
Now, watch this.

880
01:29:23,809 --> 01:29:26,437
Okay, that's enough!
That's enough!

881
01:29:26,512 --> 01:29:28,707
That's it.
The show's over.

882
01:29:28,780 --> 01:29:30,714
I'll see you back
at the Peacock.

883
01:29:33,619 --> 01:29:35,553
Get out of here.

884
01:30:02,614 --> 01:30:04,206
Here.

885
01:30:05,350 --> 01:30:06,942
Come on.

886
01:30:09,855 --> 01:30:12,790
There you are.
That's better, isn't it?

887
01:30:15,527 --> 01:30:18,189
I've done well tonight.

888
01:30:18,263 --> 01:30:21,255
Here. Buy yourself a sweet.

889
01:30:48,560 --> 01:30:49,993
My treasure.

890
01:32:09,141 --> 01:32:12,269
- I know what happened last night.
- What?

891
01:32:20,886 --> 01:32:23,088
Dear God.

892
01:32:23,088 --> 01:32:24,817
Boy!

893
01:32:42,107 --> 01:32:46,134
Where is he?
Where's Mr. Merrick?

894
01:32:51,583 --> 01:32:54,245
Where is he?
Where's Mr. Merrick?

895
01:32:56,388 --> 01:32:59,255
- I don't know what you mean, sir.
- Don't lie to me!

896
01:33:00,659 --> 01:33:03,924
I know all about it.
You were seen.

897
01:33:03,995 --> 01:33:05,929
You're involved with Bytes,
aren't you?

898
01:33:05,997 --> 01:33:08,864
You've taken him.
Where is he?

899
01:33:08,934 --> 01:33:11,903
Now, wait a minute.
I haven't taken him anywhere.

900
01:33:11,970 --> 01:33:15,531
I don't know no Bytes.
We were just having a bit of fun.

901
01:33:15,607 --> 01:33:17,598
We never hurt him.

902
01:33:17,676 --> 01:33:19,610
You know, just having a laugh,
that's all.

903
01:33:19,678 --> 01:33:22,806
You bastard! He's gone!

904
01:33:22,881 --> 01:33:25,213
When I left him,
he was in bed safe and sound!

905
01:33:25,283 --> 01:33:28,582
You bastard!
You bastard!

906
01:33:28,653 --> 01:33:32,282
You're not listening to me!
I told you, I don't know no Bytes!

907
01:33:32,357 --> 01:33:34,154
I ain't done nothing wrong.

908
01:33:34,226 --> 01:33:37,957
People pay money to see
your monster. I collect it.

909
01:33:38,029 --> 01:33:40,190
You're the monster!
You're the freak!

910
01:33:40,265 --> 01:33:42,358
Now, get out!
You're finished!

911
01:33:42,434 --> 01:33:45,926
You don't frighten me,
you and your bleedin' Elephant Man.

912
01:33:47,472 --> 01:33:50,669
I'm glad what I done,
and you can do nothing about it.

913
01:33:50,742 --> 01:33:52,972
Only Mothershead can sack me now!

914
01:33:58,784 --> 01:34:00,376
Done.

915
01:34:17,102 --> 01:34:19,093
There's something
I'd like to tell you, Treves.

916
01:34:20,238 --> 01:34:24,072
You know, I felt as deeply
as you did about John.

917
01:34:24,142 --> 01:34:25,871
Well, now he's disappeared...

918
01:34:25,944 --> 01:34:28,174
very likely to the continent.

919
01:34:28,246 --> 01:34:30,476
There's no question
of your going after him.

920
01:34:30,549 --> 01:34:33,541
You're desperately needed here
by your patients.

921
01:34:33,618 --> 01:34:36,451
You did everything
in your power.

922
01:34:36,521 --> 01:34:38,546
Remember that, Treves.

923
01:34:38,623 --> 01:34:40,557
Everything in your power.

924
01:36:10,181 --> 01:36:11,773
Get the stool.

925
01:36:38,510 --> 01:36:40,068
Get up, you bastard.

926
01:37:05,904 --> 01:37:09,670
Look at all these
beautiful animals.

927
01:37:14,179 --> 01:37:16,647
What a lot you have.

928
01:37:28,627 --> 01:37:31,152
That sly bastard.

929
01:37:36,167 --> 01:37:39,398
He's doing this to spite me!

930
01:37:49,414 --> 01:37:51,814
You're doing this to spite me...

931
01:37:51,883 --> 01:37:53,851
and it's got to stop!

932
01:37:53,918 --> 01:37:56,386
Bytes, he's sick!

933
01:37:56,454 --> 01:37:58,388
Let him die!

934
01:38:00,492 --> 01:38:03,256
But don't think
I'm going to bury that...

935
01:38:05,697 --> 01:38:07,358
bag of flesh!

936
01:38:07,432 --> 01:38:09,024
Wrong!

937
01:38:16,141 --> 01:38:18,075
As a matter of fact...

938
01:38:24,716 --> 01:38:27,344
- Bytes, no!
- As a matter of fact...

939
01:38:27,419 --> 01:38:29,353
Bytes, stop, please!

940
01:39:15,300 --> 01:39:17,791
Bytes, please, don't!

941
01:40:24,235 --> 01:40:25,827
We've decided...

942
01:40:29,073 --> 01:40:31,007
we're gonna get you out of here.

943
01:40:31,075 --> 01:40:33,202
All right?

944
01:40:59,671 --> 01:41:01,605
Good on you, mate.
Good on you.

945
01:42:21,352 --> 01:42:22,785
Luck, my friend.

946
01:42:25,456 --> 01:42:28,687
Luck. And who needs it
more than we?

947
01:43:56,414 --> 01:43:58,473
Hey, mister.

948
01:43:59,817 --> 01:44:02,911
Mister, why is your head so big?

949
01:44:07,058 --> 01:44:08,992
Why is your head so big, mister?

950
01:44:12,296 --> 01:44:15,356
Why is your head so big?
Why won't you answer me?

951
01:44:21,706 --> 01:44:23,640
Why is your head so big, mister?

952
01:44:51,936 --> 01:44:53,870
Stop him!

953
01:45:51,162 --> 01:45:54,154
I am not an animal!

954
01:45:56,033 --> 01:45:58,934
I am not an animal!

955
01:46:01,639 --> 01:46:05,268
I am a human being!

956
01:46:10,681 --> 01:46:13,479
I am...

957
01:46:13,551 --> 01:46:15,485
a man!

958
01:46:20,558 --> 01:46:22,526
Excuse me, sir.

959
01:46:22,593 --> 01:46:25,061
Out of the way, sir.
Excuse me.

960
01:46:28,065 --> 01:46:31,364
Mr. Treves, sir!
They found him!

961
01:46:31,435 --> 01:46:33,995
I think they found John!

962
01:46:45,483 --> 01:46:47,075
Thank you.

963
01:46:54,358 --> 01:46:57,088
- Keep still, girl.
- Sorry.

964
01:46:58,629 --> 01:47:02,258
That was very nice of Mrs. Kendal
to give me this dress for tonight.

965
01:47:02,333 --> 01:47:03,925
It's so beautiful.

966
01:47:07,371 --> 01:47:10,169
Does Mrs. Kendal know
that John is dying?

967
01:47:14,545 --> 01:47:16,012
Yes, she knows.

968
01:47:31,128 --> 01:47:33,596
How do I look?

969
01:47:33,664 --> 01:47:35,291
Splendid.

970
01:47:35,366 --> 01:47:39,462
Now, you will not look out of place.
You look absolutely splendid.

971
01:47:39,537 --> 01:47:43,405
- Oh, splendid. Shall we go?
- Yes.

972
01:47:44,475 --> 01:47:46,033
Again...

973
01:47:46,110 --> 01:47:50,137
I can't tell you how sorry I am
for what happened.

974
01:47:50,214 --> 01:47:53,706
You see, I had no idea, really.

975
01:47:53,784 --> 01:47:56,548
Please, you mustn't blame yourself.

976
01:47:56,621 --> 01:48:01,217
Mr. Treves, don't worry about me...

977
01:48:01,292 --> 01:48:03,453
my friend.

978
01:48:03,527 --> 01:48:09,066
I am happy every hour of the day.

979
01:48:09,066 --> 01:48:13,662
My life is full
because I know that I am loved.

980
01:48:17,508 --> 01:48:20,306
I have gained myself.

981
01:48:28,619 --> 01:48:32,316
I could not say that...

982
01:48:32,390 --> 01:48:34,449
were it not for you.

983
01:48:38,596 --> 01:48:41,997
Well, and l...

984
01:48:42,066 --> 01:48:45,934
You've done so much for me as well.

985
01:48:46,003 --> 01:48:47,595
Thank you.

986
01:48:49,940 --> 01:48:51,498
So...

987
01:48:52,643 --> 01:48:54,611
I'll fetch Mrs. Mothershead
and Nora...

988
01:48:54,679 --> 01:48:57,239
and be back in a few minutes.

989
01:48:59,684 --> 01:49:01,618
Very good, my friend.

990
01:49:06,223 --> 01:49:08,157
My friend.

991
01:52:04,001 --> 01:52:06,265
Mrs. Kendal.

992
01:52:09,206 --> 01:52:11,367
Thank you.

993
01:52:11,442 --> 01:52:13,376
Your Royal Highness...

994
01:52:13,444 --> 01:52:15,207
ladies and gentlemen...

995
01:52:15,279 --> 01:52:17,770
tonight's performance
was very special to me...

996
01:52:17,848 --> 01:52:20,373
because it was very special
to someone else.

997
01:52:20,451 --> 01:52:23,477
A man who knows the theater
and who loves the theater...

998
01:52:23,554 --> 01:52:26,489
and yet this is the very first time
he's ever been here.

999
01:52:28,192 --> 01:52:29,489
I wish to dedicate...

1000
01:52:29,593 --> 01:52:32,460
The whole company wishes to dedicate
with all their hearts...

1001
01:52:32,530 --> 01:52:34,964
tonight's performance...

1002
01:52:35,032 --> 01:52:37,000
to Mr. John Merrick...

1003
01:52:37,067 --> 01:52:39,058
my very dear friend.

1004
01:52:51,448 --> 01:52:54,417
Stand up.
They want to see you.

1005
01:52:54,485 --> 01:52:57,283
Go on. It's all right.
Just stand up.

1006
01:52:57,354 --> 01:52:59,288
They want to see you.

1007
01:53:35,726 --> 01:53:39,662
I really did believe that...

1008
01:53:39,730 --> 01:53:43,359
the ogre would never
get out of the dungeon.

1009
01:53:45,169 --> 01:53:48,661
Good.
So you really enjoyed yourself?

1010
01:53:51,442 --> 01:53:53,034
It was wonderful!

1011
01:53:53,110 --> 01:53:57,911
Good. Then we must
go again some evening.

1012
01:53:57,982 --> 01:54:01,110
Oh, yes.
Oh, I hope so.

1013
01:54:01,185 --> 01:54:03,210
Yes, we will.
We will.

1014
01:54:04,755 --> 01:54:07,121
Good. I'm pleased.

1015
01:54:07,191 --> 01:54:11,025
Well, I ought to go.

1016
01:54:11,095 --> 01:54:15,395
You must get some sleep.
Good night, and sleep well.

1017
01:54:17,601 --> 01:54:21,401
- And you too, my friend.
- Yes.

1018
01:54:21,472 --> 01:54:23,940
I'm so pleased
you enjoyed yourself.

1019
01:54:24,008 --> 01:54:26,135
Good night.

1020
01:54:29,580 --> 01:54:31,172
Good night.

1021
01:56:03,540 --> 01:56:05,098
It's finished.

1022
01:59:36,553 --> 01:59:40,887
Never, oh, never
nothing will die.

